##"Male God" Zhang Wenhong: Shanghai excellent I just pass

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Reporter trainee, Zhang Hui, Peng Youqi, reporter, Luan Xiaona Xiong Feng, Chen Si

On February 29, eight cases of COVID-19 pneumonia were discharged from the Shanghai Municipal Clinical Center for Public Health. All of them had mild illness on the same day. So far, a total of 287 cases have been cured and discharged from hospital in Shanghai, the discharge rate has exceeded 85% .

If the patient is discharged from the hospital to recover Yang, Shanghai has a plan in place, Zhang said. Filmed by Peng Youqi, edited by Zeng Yinzi 02:29

Shanghai is basically stable, but it is not completely over, Zhang Wenhong, head of the Shanghai Medical Treatment Expert Group and director of the infection department of the Mount Hua Hospital affiliated to Fudan University, said in an interview. After being discharged from the hospital today, 85% of the patients in Shanghai have basically been cured. We still have 15% of the patients here, and some of them come in later, so they're going to be out a little later.

But I think, according to the normal plan, Shanghai should be completed smoothly. But that doesn't mean the epidemic prevention work is over. There's still a lot of work to be done.

"It's really a big game. Don't think I'm saying Nice things here, that's what's going on. The whole of Shanghai has made excellent achievements in the prevention and control of the epidemic. In this prevention and control campaign, I mainly worked with my doctor brothers, who came from critical care medicine, suction medicine, infectious medicine, cardiovascular medicine, traditional Chinese medicine, nursing team, psychiatry, and the vast medical care center of the Public Health Center. In this month and more, I saw more than 300 patients here every day, so everything else was done by the whole Shanghai Prevention and control team,"Zhang said, the results of the medical staff, at this time today, 85% of the patients are discharged from the hospital, and there will be more patients discharged from the hospital every day. The overall results of the treatment, I feel worthy of the people of Shanghai, our results are passing.

"I think the first stage of Shanghai's epidemic prevention and control performance is excellent, but this is not under my command. My task is right here, with more than 300 patients, and I got 60-80 marks, " Zhang said.

#In the last 2-3 weeks, no critical cases have progressed to critical condition in Shanghai

In an interview with media reporters, Zhang Wenhong also mentioned the importance of pathological research.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
He pointed out that before this, we had held a pathological anatomy conference, and also had a discussion with the pathological anatomy team of Professor Zhao Jingmin from Beijing, who is also the first research team in the world to publish a pathological article, through their pathological research, we're going to find out exactly how to treat it.

"In the last two to three weeks, there has not been a single case of severe illness in Shanghai that has progressed to critical illness, " he said. "This comes from our understanding of the pathology of the disease, and through direct dialogue with pathologists, we have further confirmed that some of the details in the Shanghai plan are reasonable. ".

The pathology doesn't mean a machine can suck the dirt out of the CAPILLARY, he said. He doesn't agree. "There's no science to it, but it's become mainstream on the Internet, and I think it's a very irresponsible promotion of medicine, and I think real medicine is a very professional team, thinking deeply, in a language that you don't understand, and then coming up with treatments that you don't understand, and ultimately bringing patients back to life. "

#How does the reexamination after patient discharge carry out? Will it spread again after Yang-yang?

Zhang Wenhong said that the re-examination of patients with new coronary pneumonia, taken from the throat swab, is the throat. The larynx is positive once every time, when the viral load is very high, but of course a very small percentage of patients who are critically discharged, will continue to have low viral loads, which is one possibility. The second possibility is whether the sample is of good quality.

"So there are a very small number of patients who go from being negative twice to being positive when they leave the hospital. This is not surprising, but this positive, we should not focus on the negative or positive, nor to find the complete virus or nucleic acid fragments, I personally do not think it matters."

People should care about the most essential things, Zhang said. If you go for a meal and you're starving, you don't ask if it's Shandong or Shanghai Food, you just ask if it's full. So, for this viral disease, it's really a question of whether it's going to spread. "So we are very concerned about whether these patients have been discharged and recovered, and whether they have been passed on to other people? Now, according to the national data, none of them. That is what we should be concerned about. "

Zhang Wenhong said that in response to this matter, Shanghai has made a preparatory plan very early, namely after two nucleic acid negative, will also give the patient to do the dry swab at the same time. In other words, you have nucleic acid swallowed, the mouth, stool, intestinal tract may have this virus, so all to be negative.

In Shanghai, two weeks after discharge from the hospital, there will be another sampling and a return visit. "But I can tell you today that so far, there has been no re-emergence of Yang in Shanghai, but this does not mean that the patients behind us have not re-emergence of Yang, this is difficult to say. But what I care about is, what if it comes back? So I am only concerned about whether patients returning to Yang will spread again. This is the first point. So far, I have not seen this data,"Zhang added, the second point, for the patient who returns Yang already made the reserve. For patients returning to Yang, in order to be safe, although there is no risk of transmission, but will give him isolation, eat well, live well, observation for two weeks, two weeks after discharge, a good recovery. "So I don't think this is a very big problem, but we have to be careful. "

#Shanghai Chinese and Western medicine is very harmonious, what is effective to the patient to take who

Zhang Wenhong in an interview with reporters, said the plasma therapy is the Shanghai team in Wuhan first began to do. Ten cases have been done and are still being done, and a few cases have been treated with plasma therapy at public health centres. "The conclusion that can be drawn at this point is that the patient in this critical condition, when treated with plasma therapy, can promote the virus to turn negative, which is what we expected, but I will say again, any treatment is only a part of the treatment, there is no scenario in the world like the one in the movies -- The patient will magically recover, sit up, eat and walk, it's impossible, it's impossible. "

Zhang Wenhong further explained that all convalescent plasma, is hoped that can pass a few specific antibodies, give this patient the ability, the virus neutralizes, promote his turn negative. For example, it used to take 5 to 10 days to turn overcast, but now it can take 3 to 5 days, and the improvement rate is very limited. "So plasma therapy, may be able to promote negative conversion in early patients, but for late patients, we're just saying it helps us to promote negative conversion in critically ill patients, and it helps us, and it's by no means saying that with one plasma treatment today, all [ other ] treatments don't matter. So it would be inaccurate to say that if someone had suggested that all the patients could be saved with this treatment."

In the case of Shanghai, it is a very clear integration of the strength of all disciplines team, every subject of Western medicine, severe disease, aspiration, infection, heart, all here together doing, every team of TCM here is also very serious about how to make the patient recover more quickly, shorten his discharge days, how to promote the stability of his inner environment.

The average length of stay in Shanghai is 14 days, Zhang said. Shanghai team of Chinese and Western medicine, working together in harmony. "You can interview every Chinese doctor, because there is no school of thought here, " he said. "We just talk about what is good for the patient and what is good for the patient. So it's very harmonious here. " The holistic approach is the ultimate consensus, and the treatment of critically ill patients depends on all of the forces working together. "The fact that 85 per cent of the patients in Shanghai are cured means that most patients can be cured relatively easily, but it also depends on various teams, both TCM and Western medicine. "
